ad, as which also the human body is easily understood, is from the common Aramaic טוּנָא (ṭūna, ṭunnā), an assimilated form of טְוּעֲנָא (ṭūʕănā), טְעוּנָא (ṭəʕūnā, “load, burden”), which or a similar form is also the source of طَاعُون (ṭāʕūn, “plague”)."}, "ipa": ["/tˤann/", "/tˤunn/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n27138", "headword_ar": "طَنَّ", "root": "Tn", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (MA, Msb, K, TA,) aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, TA,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaniynN", "text_ar": "طَنِينٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v. infrà], (MA, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It made a sound"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a continued"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a reiterated kind, and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "either"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "low"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sharp"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (MA, Msb, K, TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tn~n", "text_ar": "طنّن", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TanoTana", "text_ar": "طَنْطَنَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tan~a Al*~ubaAbu", "text_ar": "طَنَّ الذُّبَابُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TanoTana", "text_ar": "طَنْطَنَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dan~a", "text_ar": "دَنَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "danodana", "text_ar": "دَنْدَنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The flies made a"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "humming,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "buzzing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "t